&lt;p&gt;Another thing.&lt;br&gt;We are also using a Game Engine that, while it is popular for making fan-games, is hardly used for game development anymore. Don’t get me wrong, &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rpgmakerweb.com/products/rpg-maker-xp&#34;&gt;RPG Maker XP&lt;/a&gt; is a good engine, it is just… “old”. &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.rpgmakerweb.com/products/rpg-maker-mz&#34;&gt;Especially now that the new version of RPG Maker just came out on the 20th&lt;/a&gt;. But hey. I like the engine. And now I think it is time to end the post because I am running out of things to talk about.&lt;/p&gt;
